The paper deals with the problem of localization, which is a common topic in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on time-of-arrival based localization, which is a subfield of localization that involves measuring the time it takes for signals to travel from anchors to a target location. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SY, cs.MA, and cs.LG.
